(15036, 'Placing an ad through radio is cheaper than other options.', 'A: True', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15037, 'Public relations stunts’ objective is to persuade the masses of the good intentions of a brand, company or individual.', 'A: True', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15038, 'Motion picture recording happens during which of the following stages of production?', 'A: Production', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15039, 'The Story Editor is part of which part of the film production process?', 'A: Pre-production', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15040, 'A life insurance company in Thailand has released an advertisement that shows the life of a man who had nothing but had so much to give other people, even without anything in exchange. The twist at the end revealed that the kid he gave his money to has returned to school. The lines at the end evoked the feeling of believing in the inherent good in people. This commercial is an example of ______.', 'A: Plain folks', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15041, 'What\\\'s the task of the Production Manager?', 'A: Handles all of the physical elements of production from the actors to the location', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15042, 'The account manager is the one who meets with the client at the beginning of the transaction for an advertisement.', 'A: True', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15043, 'Japanese commercials are known for their absurdity and creativity. This is a sample commercial for the famous Nissin’s Cup Noodle: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NuX8ZRxJIF0. Based on how it was advertised, the commercial is an example of _____.', 'A: Glittering generalities', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15044, 'A link to a story has been shared through Facebook with the headline, “Juan Ponce Enrile has died.\\ This is an example of ____.', 'A: Hoax', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15045, 'Shiseido, a famous skincare and makeup brand in Japan, launched a new commercial. It is set in a school where the teacher and the students are made to look pretty using the brand’s famed products. When the first part of the commercial ended, the second part begins when the video is rewinded to show that the ladies in the beginning are actually men in drag, including the teacher. This commercial is an example of ______.', 'A: Bandwagon', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
(15046, 'Which of the following is not a type of animation technique?', 'A: None of the choices', 'MEIL-122 (Media and Information Literacy)', NULL),
