(17039, 'A simple pendulum, 2.0 m in length, is released with a push when the support string is at an angle of 25° from the vertical. If the initial speed of the suspended mass is 2.0 m/s when at the release point, what is its speed at the bottom of the swing? (g = 9.8 m/s2)', '2.8 m/s', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
(17040, 'A rocket of total mass M and with burnout mass 0.15 M attains a speed of 3,500 m/s after starting from rest in deep space. What is the exhaust velocity of the rocket?', '11,666.67 m/s', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
(17041, 'A system of 3 masses is located as follows: m1 = m0 at (0, L), m2 = 2m0 at the origin, and m3 = 3m0 at (3L, 0). Where is the center of mass of these masses?', '24°', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
(17042, 'Two satellites are monitored as they orbit the Earth; satellite X is eight times as far from the Earth\\\'s center as is satellite Y. From Kepler\\\'s third law one may conclude that the period or revolution of X is what factor times that of Y?', '22.6', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
(17043, 'A stone is thrown with an initial speed of 15 m/s at an angle of 53° above the horizontal from the top of a 40-m building. If g = 9.8 m/s2 and air resistance is negligible, then what is the speed of the rock as it hits the ground?', '32 m/s', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
(17044, 'A 7.0-kg bowling ball strikes a 2.0-kg pin. The pin flies forward with a velocity of 6.0 m/s; the ball continues forward at 5.0 m/s. What was the original velocity of the ball?', '6.7 m/s', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
(17045, 'Two blocks of masses 24 kg and 9 kg are connected together by a light string and rest on a frictionless level surface. Attached to the 9-kg mass is another light string, which a person uses to pull both blocks horizontally. If the two-block system accelerates at 0.6 m/s2 what is the tension in the connecting string between the blocks?', '14.4 N', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
