(17066, 'A pile driver drives a post into the ground. The mass of the pile driver is 2,800 kg and it is dropped through a height of 7.0 m on each stroke. If the resisting force of the ground is 5.0 x 106 N, how far is the post driven in on each stroke?', '9.6 x 1024 kg (​3.8 cm)', 'PHYC-121 (Physics)', NULL),
